SIMPLE: lightweight
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lightweight
<hw>Light"weight`</hw> <pr>(l⟦imac⟧t"w⟦amac⟧t`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>One of less than average weight;</def> <specif>specif.:</specif>
<def>In boxing, wrestling, etc., one weighing not more than 133 pounds
(U. S. amateur rules 135 pounds, Eng. 140 pounds).</def>
<wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A person of small importance or mental ability,
especially one who is unimportant but cheeky and presumptuous.</def>
<wns>[wns=2]</wns> <mark>[Colloq., Chiefly U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> whippersnapper, jackanapes.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>a wrestler who weighs 139-154 pounds.</def>
<wns>[wns=3]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lightweight</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Lightweight
<hw>Light"weight`</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Light in weight,
as a coin; specif., applied to a man or animal who is a
lightweight.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>made of thin cloth, of relatively little weight; --
of clothing or fabrics; <as>as, <ex>lightweight</ex> fabrics</as>.</def>
<wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Light-winged</ent>⟦br⟧
